   <mods:abstract>Franklin has not heard of the Act of Congress which Jay mentioned in his
            last letter. Colonel Diricks stopped here on his way to Holland but mentioned nothing of
            his business in Holland except to see his friends. Franklin agrees that the expedition
            to Canada ought to be deferred. Recommends La Luzerne. News from England is that the
            fear of a war with Spain is beginning to create a general disposition for
            peace.</mods:abstract>
